data.title: Lance Corporal Frank Gilbert Usher
data.text:
Lance Corporal Frank Gilbert Usher (337, 21st Coy, Australian Machine Gun Corps) was born 7 January 1900 in Oakey, Queensland. He was working as a woodcutter near Toowoomba when he enlisted in March 1916. Frank died of wounds received in the battle of Menin Road on 20 September 1917. He was buried in the Belgian Battery Military Cemetery, but his grave was not able to be located after the war. Frank is commemorated on the Ypres (Menin Gate) Memorial, Belgium. He was 17 years 8 months. Frankâ€™s brother Corporal Ralph Richard Usher was wounded at Noreuil in March 1917.
